arch:property.oc:show_val: Flot Smpl 2 (4387) Diagnostics only A medium-sized room infill unit. The unit is generally medium brown and slightly mixed, with a few heavily weathered fragments, and a few possibly trampled pieces mixed in with more typical fill. In general not much rolling or abrasion but a lot of digestion. There are a lot of digested vertebra fragments, and most diagnostic long bones fragments are digested slivers. About 3% low temperature burning. The fragment size is medium with as many 3 and 4 cm as 2 cm. It is perhaps slightly disturbed house fill. At least a third of the unit is diagnostic, primarily caprid feet and teeth but there is a reasonable amount of pelvis and scapula and a few diagnostic long bone fragments from both fore and hind limb. There is also a complete cattle C+4, a fragmentary cow tooth, a fox pelvis with skinning cut marks and two roe deer phalanx. Ribs and vertebrae are mainly sheep size and relatively common considering the size of the unit. The flot sample is medium to light brown with a large amount (3%?) of digestion and about 5% low temperature burning. There is one bird bone that was pulled for export. All the other diagnostics were caprid. in the flot sample the edges look fairly sharp and there is not much abrasion or rolling. The context as a whole seems like generally undisturbed fill with some inclusions. Last Number = 121

arch:string.div: The unique identifier for each contextual unit, matching those used in the central Çatalhöyük excavation database and in publications. The excavation uses single-context recording.
